column4: I have a question about ubuntu. Is this the right place to ask it?
While installing ubuntu I accidentally installed it to my 32gb sd card. Of course the SSD in my computer is also 32GB and i was able to reinstall it to my SDD
but now the computer wont see the SD card and i cant even format it on my Windows machine
I dont see the SD under ubuntu
I installed Gparted and it doesnt show the SDHC card at all
597.384439] mmc0: error -110 whilst initialising SD card
597.384439] mmc0: error -110 whilst initialising SD card
Do you know what error -110 whilst initializing SD card means?
